  "answer": "Sales of property belonging to others without their permission are suspended (muwqaf) until the owner's approval. If the owner approves, the sale is valid and ownership transfers. If the owner rejects, the sale is void. The buyer may have rights depending on the owner's decision. (Source: Sections on sale of third-party property and conditions of approval, pages 60-70)",
  "block_id": "2|FATAWA-QAZI-KHAN-02_hocr_searchtext.txt.gz|0|1-2",
  "block_num": "0",
  "end_page": "2",
  "interpretation": "This principle protects property rights by requiring owner consent for sales, preventing unauthorized dispossession.",
  "modern_usage": "This principle aligns with modern property laws requiring clear title and owner consent for valid sales, preventing fraud and disputes.",
