[2025-05-25T13:25:10.794Z] Full metadata: {
  "answer": "Salam contracts require the sale and purchase wording with specific conditions, including the existence of the sold item from the contract time until the delivery time without interruption. The sold item must be specified in quantity and quality, and the payment is made in advance. Certain items like similar quantities and weights are permissible, while others like animals or heterogeneous items are not. The contract remains valid despite the death of the seller but not the buyer. The buyer has options if the item is not delivered on time. (Source: Salam contract conditions and rules, pages 4-13)",
  "block_id": "2|FATAWA-QAZI-KHAN-02_hocr_searchtext.txt.gz|0|1-2",
  "block_num": "0",
  "end_page": "2",
  "interpretation": "The Salam contract ensures fairness by requiring the existence and specification of the sold item and advance payment, protecting both parties from uncertainty and fraud.",
  "modern_usage": "In modern finance, Salam contracts can be applied in forward sales of commodities where payment is made upfront and delivery is deferred, such as agricultural products or manufacturing goods, ensuring clarity and risk management.",
